
Enable HROMA (Hitachi Remote Ops Monitor Agent) for Hitachi VSP B26 & VSP E590

⸻

🔹 Change Type

Standard Change (Low Risk – Monitoring Enablement)

⸻

🔹 Objective

To enable remote monitoring and call-home functionality for:
	•	Hitachi VSP B26
	•	Hitachi VSP E590

This will allow proactive alerting, automatic ticketing, and health monitoring via Hitachi Support.

⸻

🔹 Scope
	•	Configure HROMA agent on monitoring server
	•	Add storage systems (VSP B26 & VSP E590)
	•	Enable SNMP communication
	•	Enable secure transport (HTTPS)
	•	Validate communication and monitoring

⸻

🔹 Pre-Checks
	1.	Verify HROMA installation:
	•	Access URL: http://localhost:6696
	•	Confirm agent is running
	2.	Verify network connectivity:
	•	HROMA → Storage (Ping + SNMP port 161)
	•	HROMA → Internet (HTTPS 443)
	3.	Collect required details:
	•	Site ID
	•	Storage IPs (GUM/SVP)
	•	SNMP community / credentials
	4.	Take backup / screenshots of current state

⸻

🔹 Implementation Steps

✅ Step 1: Login to HROMA
	•	Open browser → http://localhost:6696
	•	Login using Administrator

⸻

✅ Step 2: Configure Base Settings

Go to:
👉 Configuration → Base
	•	Enter:
	•	Site ID
	•	Scan Interval (150 sec recommended)
	•	Daily report time
	•	Save configuration

⸻

✅ Step 3: Configure Transport (Call-Home)

Go to:
👉 Configuration → Transport Agents
	•	Enable HTTPS transport
	•	Configure proxy (if required)
	•	Save

⸻

✅ Step 4: Configure SNMP on Storage

On VSP B26 & VSP E590:
	•	Enable SNMP Agent
	•	Add HROMA server IP
	•	Configure:
	•	SNMP v2 or v3
	•	Community string (e.g., public)

⸻

✅ Step 5: Add Storage Devices

Go to:
👉 Summary → Add Device

Fill details:

For VSP B26:
	•	Device Type: VSP E Series
	•	IP (SVP/GUM)
	•	Site ID
	•	Communication Type: SVP

For VSP E590:
	•	Device Type: VSP E Series
	•	GUM IPs:
	•	Primary & Secondary
	•	Communication Type: GUM / SVP

Click Add

⸻

✅ Step 6: Configure Credentials

Go to:
👉 User Management
	•	Add SNMP credentials
	•	Map credentials to devices

⸻

✅ Step 7: Verify Device Status

Go to:
👉 Summary

Check:
	•	Device Status = ✅ Device Okay
	•	No Comms Error

⸻

✅ Step 8: Test Communication

Go to:
👉 Transport History
	•	Click Request Report
	•	Verify:
	•	Status = Success

⸻

🔹 Post-Validation
	•	Devices visible in HROMA
	•	No communication errors
	•	Successful transport logs
	•	Monitoring enabled

⸻

🔹 Rollback Plan

If issue occurs:
	1.	Remove added devices from HROMA
	2.	Disable transport agent
	3.	Restore previous SNMP settings on storage
	4.	Stop HROMA service (if required)
